featured_reviews.review_id: Major Muslim cemetery of Etawah. It has a mosque inside of it to offer Salah. Greenery, sitting palces and tap water to drink are available. There are 22 Khwajas or Lords are buried here that are supposed to belong to Muhammad Ghori of  12th century AD, according to a folklore. They were the Khwajas who fought , as it is believed, and got killed. They are the Shaheed. Many people who crossed the Kabristan at night  claimed to watched them in their armour with blood.  The four walls sorrounding the 22 graves are of very ancient. The 22 graves are so haphazardly situated that it becomes difficult to count them upto the number 22 correctly. People try but fail, such is the belief. There is a well also which has been unused for a long time.

Also it would have been better if authorities could straighten the road just outside the premises, there's a blind turn and it leads to a lot of accidents. I wonder why local administration never bothered with it!
